# Custom Domain Setup — coparenthub.co.za on Render

This document records how the `coparenthub.co.za` domain was connected to our
Render-hosted app, including the issue we hit along the way and how it was
resolved. Keep this updated if the setup ever changes (e.g. moving registrars,
adding subdomains, re-enabling proxying, etc.).

## Summary

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Domain | `coparenthub.co.za` |
| Registrar | HostAfrica |
| DNS Host | Cloudflare (Free plan) |
| App Host | Render (Web Service) |
| Render app subdomain | `coparenthub-web.onrender.com` |
| SSL | Auto-issued by Render after domain verification |

## Why we needed Cloudflare in the middle

The domain was registered directly with **HostAfrica**, but a domain-only
account (no hosting plan) does not include a DNS Zone Editor — only a
**Nameservers** page. Render requires the ability to add/edit `CNAME`/`A`
records directly, which HostAfrica's domain-only panel doesn't expose.

**Fix:** Point the domain's nameservers to a free **Cloudflare** account,
which gives full DNS record management at no cost, and manage the actual
`CNAME` records there instead of at HostAfrica.

## Step-by-step: what we did

### 1. Add the custom domain in Render
- Render Dashboard → select the web service → **Settings → Custom Domains**
  → **+ Add Custom Domain**.
- Added both:
  - `coparenthub.co.za` (root/apex domain)
  - `www.coparenthub.co.za`
- Render generated the required DNS targets:
  - `www` → CNAME → `coparenthub-web.onrender.com`
  - `@` (root) → CNAME → `coparenthub-web.onrender.com`
    (fallback: A record → `216.24.57.1` if CNAME/ANAME isn't supported by the
    DNS provider)

### 2. Create a free Cloudflare account and add the domain
- Signed up at cloudflare.com → **Add a Site** → `coparenthub.co.za`.
- Selected the **Free plan**.
- Cloudflare scanned for existing DNS records (none of consequence found).
- Cloudflare assigned two nameservers:
  - `dawn.ns.cloudflare.com`
  - `viddy.ns.cloudflare.com`

### 3. Add DNS records in Cloudflare
Under **DNS → Records**, added:

| Type | Name | Target | Proxy status | TTL |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| CNAME | `@` | `coparenthub-web.onrender.com` | **DNS only** (grey cloud) | Auto |
| CNAME | `www` | `coparenthub-web.onrender.com` | **DNS only** (grey cloud) | Auto |

> **Important:** Proxy status must be set to **DNS only** (grey cloud), not
> **Proxied** (orange cloud). If proxying is left on, Render cannot verify
> domain ownership or issue an SSL certificate, since Render needs to see
> the DNS resolve directly to it. Proxying can be turned on later once the
> domain is verified and the certificate is issued, if Cloudflare's
> CDN/WAF features are wanted — but leave it off for now.

### 4. Update nameservers at HostAfrica
- HostAfrica → **My Domains** → `coparenthub.co.za` → **Manage** →
  **Nameservers**.
- Replaced HostAfrica's default nameservers with Cloudflare's:
  - `dawn.ns.cloudflare.com`
  - `viddy.ns.cloudflare.com`
- Removed any other/default nameservers listed.
- Saved changes.

### 5. Wait for propagation
- Cloudflare estimates **1–2 hours**, but it can take up to **24 hours**
  depending on the registrar.
- Cloudflare emails automatically once it detects the domain is active on
  its nameservers.

### 6. Verify in Render
- Once Cloudflare shows the domain as active, return to Render's
  **Custom Domains** section and click **Verify**.
- On success, Render automatically issues a free TLS/SSL certificate for
  the domain.

## Issues encountered

### Issue: Render domain verification failed initially
**Symptom:** Render showed *"We weren't able to verify coparenthub.co.za"*
right after adding the domain.

**Cause:** No DNS records had been added yet at that point — HostAfrica's
domain-only account had no DNS Zone Editor, so there was nowhere to add the
CNAME records Render needed.

**Resolution:** Moved DNS management to Cloudflare (free plan) by switching
nameservers at HostAfrica, then added the CNAME records in Cloudflare
instead.

### Issue: HostAfrica has no DNS Zone Editor on domain-only accounts
**Symptom:** Sidebar only showed **Nameservers**, **Auto Renew**, **Addons**,
etc. — no "DNS Zone Editor" or "Manage DNS" option.

**Cause:** DNS zone editing at HostAfrica appears to be tied to having an
active hosting plan with them, not just a domain registration.

**Resolution:** Used Cloudflare as an external DNS manager instead of relying
on HostAfrica's panel. This is free and gives full control over records.

## Notes for future reference

- If we ever add more subdomains (e.g. `api.coparenthub.co.za`,
  `app.coparenthub.co.za`), add them the same way: create the custom domain
  in Render first to get the exact target value, then add a matching CNAME
  record in Cloudflare with proxy status set to DNS only until verified.
- Do not add an `AAAA` record — Render does not support IPv6, and an AAAA
  record can cause verification/routing issues.
- If we ever want Cloudflare's CDN/WAF/DDoS protection (orange-cloud
  proxying) after the domain is verified and SSL is issued, that can be
  turned on per record in Cloudflare DNS settings, but should be tested since
  the current Render integration is DNS-only.
- Domain renews annually at HostAfrica — first renewal due
  **July 7th, 2027**. Nameservers stay pointed at Cloudflare regardless of
  where the domain is renewed, unless we deliberately change them back.
